InputS= witch

InputSwitch is used to select a boolean value.

Input Style

<= label for=3D"input_outlined">Outlined
<= /div>

import {InputSwitch} from 'primereact/in=
putswitch';
    Getting Started

    InputSwitch is used as a controlle= d input with checked and onChange properties.

    
<InputSwitch checked=3D{this.state.value} onC=
hange=3D{(e) =3D> this.setState=
({value: e.value})} />
    Properties
    <= /tr><= /tr>=
    NameTypeDefaultD= escription
    idstringnullUnique identifier of the element.
    stylestr= ingnullInline style of the element.
    clas= sNamestringnullStyle class of the element.
    inputIdstringnullIdentifier of the i= nput element.
    namestringnullNam= e of the input element.
    checkedbooleanfa= lseSpecifies whether a inputswitch should be checked or not.
    disabledbooleanfalseWhen present, it= specifies that the component should be disabled.
    tooltip<= /td>anynullContent of the tooltip.
    t= ooltipOptionsobjectnullConfiguration of the tool= tip, refer to the tooltip documentation for more information.
    ariaLabelledBystringnullEstablishes relation= ships between the component and label(s) where its value should be one or m= ore element IDs.
    Events
    Parameters<= /table>
    Styling

    Following is the list of structural style c= lasses, for theming classes visit theming page.

    NameDescription
    onChangeevent.originalEvent: Browser event
    event.value: Checked state as= a boolean.    		Callback to invoke on value change.
    on= Focusevent: Browser event.Callback to invoke when the ele= ment receives focus.
    onBlurevent: Browser event.<= /td>Callback to invoke when the element loses focus.
    = =
    NameElement
    p-inputswitchContainer element.
    p-inputswitch-checkedContainer element in active state.
    p-inputswitch-sliderSlider element behind the handle.=
